{
  "local_port": 53806,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops in London?",
  "response": "London boasts a vibrant coffee scene with a mix of well-established favorites and trendy newcomers. Here\u2019s a list of some of the best coffee shops in the city, known for their quality coffee, ambiance, and unique offerings:\n\n### 1. **Monmouth Coffee Company**\n   - **Locations:** Covent Garden, Bermondsey, Borough Market\n   - **Why Visit:** Known for sourcing and roasting their own beans, Monmouth offers a consistently excellent cup of coffee. Their Covent Garden location is iconic and often bustling with locals and visitors alike.\n\n### 2. **Workshop Coffee**\n   - **Locations:** Clerkenwell, Marylebone, Fitzrovia, Holborn\n   - **Why Visit:** Workshop Coffee is celebrated for its meticulous approach to brewing and roasting. Their seasonal menu and sleek, modern spaces make them a favorite among coffee connoisseurs.\n\n### 3. **The Attendant**\n   - **Locations:** Fitzrovia, Shoreditch\n   - **Why Visit:** Housed in a converted Victorian public toilet, The Attendant offers a quirky yet cozy setting. They serve high-quality coffee and delicious brunch options.\n\n### 4. **Ozone Coffee Roasters**\n   - **Locations:** Shoreditch, London Fields\n   - **Why Visit:** Ozone is known for its in-house roasting and sustainable practices. Their Shoreditch location features a large open space, perfect for working or catching up with friends.\n\n### 5. **Kaffeine**\n   - **Locations:** Fitzrovia, Oxford Circus\n   - **Why Visit:** Kaffeine is an Australian-style coffee shop that has been a staple in London\u2019s coffee scene for over a decade. They serve expertly crafted espresso-based drinks and delightful pastries.\n\n### 6. **Allpress Espresso**\n   - **Locations:** Dalston, Shoreditch, Redchurch Street\n   - **Why Visit:** Originating from New Zealand, Allpress has made a name for itself in London with its rich, smooth coffee. Their Redchurch Street location is particularly popular.\n\n### 7. **Prufrock Coffee**\n   - **Location:** Leather Lane\n   - **Why Visit:** Founded by World Barista Champion Gwilym Davies, Prufrock Coffee is a must-visit for those serious about their coffee. They also offer barista training and coffee workshops.\n\n### 8. **Farm Girl Caf\u00e9**\n   - **Locations:** Notting Hill, Chelsea, Belgravia\n   - **Why Visit:** Known for its Instagram-worthy aesthetic, Farm Girl Caf\u00e9 offers a range of artisanal coffees, including trendy options like rose lattes and turmeric lattes.\n\n### 9. **TAP Coffee**\n   - **Locations:** Tottenham Court Road, Rathbone Place\n   - **Why Visit:** TAP Coffee is a local favorite, offering a simple yet high-quality coffee experience. Their minimalist approach lets the coffee shine.\n\n### 10. **Watch House**\n   - **Locations:** Bermondsey, Tower Bridge, Borough Market\n   - **Why Visit:** Watch House combines stunning design with exceptional coffee. Their Bermondsey location, in particular, is a beautiful spot to enjoy a cup.\n\n### 11. **Department of Coffee and Social Affairs**\n   - **Locations:** Multiple locations across London\n   - **Why Visit:** With a focus on ethical sourcing and community engagement, this chain offers a welcoming atmosphere and consistently great coffee.\n\n### 12. **Grind**\n   - **Locations:** Shoreditch, Soho, Holborn, and more\n   - **Why Visit:** Grind is known for its stylish interiors and all-day coffee and cocktail menus. Their signature espresso martini is a must-try.\n\n### 13. **Lightbox Caf\u00e9**\n   - **Location:** Euston\n   - **Why Visit:** Lightbox Caf\u00e9 is a specialty coffee shop that emphasizes precision and quality. Their focus on single-origin coffees makes it a haven for coffee purists.\n\n### 14. **Clerkenwell Grind**\n   - **Location:** Clerkenwell\n   - **Why Visit:** Combining a caf\u00e9 and a cocktail bar, Clerkenwell Grind offers a chic environment and a great selection of coffee and pastries.\n\n### 15. **Caravan**\n   - **Locations:** Exmouth Market, King\u2019s Cross, Fitzrovia, and more\n   - **Why Visit:** Caravan is a blend of a coffee roastery and a restaurant, offering a fantastic brunch menu alongside expertly brewed coffee.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Timing:** Some of these spots can get crowded, especially on weekends, so consider visiting during off-peak hours.\n- **Seasonal Specials:** Many of these coffee shops offer seasonal drinks and rotating roasts, so there\u2019s always something new to try.\n- **Sustainability:** Look out for cafes that prioritize ethical sourcing and sustainability, a growing trend in London\u2019s coffee scene.\n\nWhether you\u2019re a local or a visitor, these coffee shops provide some of the best coffee experiences London has to offer. Enjoy your coffee adventure!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
